modules.description: Generates and links a Rust static library as part of the build process. It interacts with build systems to embed compiled Rust code into the target environment. This function is used to integrate Rust components into OCaml projects requiring low-level system access.

Generates build configuration files and manages the compilation of Rust code into static libraries for OCaml interoperability. Processes Rust crate metadata and OCaml interface definitions to create compatible linking artifacts. Enables seamless integration of Rust dependencies into OCaml projects using standard build tools like Dune and Cargo.

Embeds compiled Rust static libraries into OCaml projects, enabling low-level system interactions through seamless integration with build systems. It handles the compilation, linking, and embedding of Rust code, allowing OCaml programs to leverage Rust's performance and safety. Key data types include compiled library artifacts and build configuration structures, with operations for linking and embedding. Users can compile Rust code once and dynamically incorporate it into OCaml applications for system-level tasks.
